name: TEMPAT Coffee and Roastery
address: Jl. Bedugul No.35, Sidakarya, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80224, Indonesia
review 1:
Food is tasty, should try the mendoan. They have a lot variety of menu from snack to dessert.
Service is super duper nice, helpful and attentive.
Atmosphere is nice, plenty of seatings for group and personal. A lot of books for a coffee break while Work from Cafe.
Payment available in cash and cashless.
review 2:
New favourite spot in Denpasar.

Food and drinks were nice. Please add more finger food variety. Pastry maybe?

I love the breezy atmosphere though I wish there was a designated smoking room rather than let them smoke in the garden. It's such a waste of fresh air.

Overall I like it here and will definitely coming back to work or read.
review 3:
If you've read The Island of the Missing Trees, you'll know how fitting this place to the tavern in the book (only it's not selling any alcohol). ü•∫üçÉ

Seems like I found new places every other week, lol. Cozy for work and reading alone. Too bad they're only open until 8pm.

What I ordered:

Coffee: 30k (ok)
Pisang goreng gula bali: 25k (tasted amazing)
review 4: Totally in love with this place. The service is great, the staffs are so friendly and helpful. The price is reasonable. The food is also great. Nasi Ayam Suksma is recommended though it's a bit spicy for someone who doesn't enjoy spicy food like me, and Chicken Karaage&Fries they're so crunchy and tasty! They have high-speed WiFi. I conducted a speed test and it was around 50 Mbps! Quiet and comfortable environment and a very nice place for anyone who's looking for a workplace outside of their house. There's an indoor area with AC which is perfect.  I definitely will come back anytime I get bored working from home.
review 5: It wouldn‚Äôt be nice for me to gatekeep this place but I don‚Äôt want it to get too crowded because it‚Äôs just so nice that you finally find a coffee shop where you can be quite with yourself (it‚Äôs SO HARD for me to find one here in Bali) great coffee, good food (not exquisite but super okay, I just wish they have more variety). I just LOOOOVE the place because it‚Äôs so airy breezy with joglo & garden. I really like the mini library spot upstair, so nice for you to hide from the crowd. All the staffs are really nice too. If I can improve one thing, it would be the closet in the toilet because it looks dirty. But the rest are perfect, will definitely recommend this to my closed ones because I trust them not to make this lovely place noisy hehe

name: Kober Mie Setan
address: Jl. Bedugul No.37A, Sidakarya, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80224, Indonesia
review 1:
What I can said, it was spicy even with only few chili.

Place is big and price is cheep. In addition, other than spicy noodle they also sold some type of dim sum and few drinks.

The taste was not bad but nothing special except for the level of spiciness. But worth it to try.
review 2: Beside their annoying waitress which is a bit lack of manners, their noodles were not bad. They offer you with only one main menu with spicy leveling and some side dishes and quite inexpensive.
review 3: Food was okay. All i can say i like gacoan more. But anyway the menu get more variation than gacoan. I dont like when the waiters call and shouting your name to find you.
review 4:
Sorry, but i never ever make bad review for a meals before, but this is just horrible, it only taste spicy with nothing else, the noodle doesn't even had any seasoning perhaps?
I waited too long for my other side dishes, and they left them out in the first floor, while they deliver other ppl meals to their table, waiting for my gf to pick it up ourself, while i already told them i was upstairs.

Well it is true, what can you expect with those prices?
But please you had other competitors than serve better than this in the range of your prices also.
review 5: Here you find all levels of spicy noodles... There are two types : "mie setan" and "mie iblis". Both taste are good. The dim sum on the other hand is not recommended.

review 1:
stayed there for a month and decided not to continue. The place is cosy, garden is huge, easy to find local foods.

name: Puri Bali Car Rental
address: Jl. Bedugul Gg. Cendrawasih No.9a, Sidakarya, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80224, Indonesia
review 1: Puri Bali service has been amazing! We had Mr Ditya for 2 days. Hes very professional we are so happy to have him. Excellent communication and super efficient. Highly recommend them. 5 star!!
review 2: Of all car rental providers I checked with, Puri Bali Car Rental was the best and reasonable. The price was competitive too. No deposits and hassle free. They took us from the harbour and we dropped the car at the airport. Very punctual as they came earlier than scheduled too. I needed to withdraw cash as ALL rental car providers only accept cash or bank transfer (which is unlikely for foreigners as it would take days to clear). The person who gave us the car brought us to the ATM place. So if you need to rent a car in Bali, get this one as i already compared woth 5 others.
review 3: Puri Bali Car Rental has been absolutely amazing! From the admin up to the drivers have been so helpful such that I did have a great time during my vacation in Bali. The price is very reasonable and competitive compared to the others. The drivers were very punctual and they arrived at my hotel 1 hour prior (I ordered 2x so I got different drivers (Pak Adit and Pak Putu) and both were punctual, communicative and helpful). The cars were clean and in good condition. Thank you for your help and I will use your service again if I visit Bali in the future. Highly recommended - refer to my 5 stars above!
review 4:
I‚Äôm a repeat customer of Puri Bali and I will be going back!!
Their car is always new and pleasant to drive. Their drivers are also friendly and great!
Bli Gede Adi is really knowledgeable and skilful. He is always early and patient, which is such a plus when travelling with a large group.
We did not have to worry about anything when it comes to transport as he always makes sure he takes care of it.
Great driver and great experience!
review 5: The driver, Eka was very helpful even though he doesn't speak much English, he tried his best to communicate with us and give us the best service. I would definitely recommend Puri Bali Car rental especially driver Ekaüëçüëç
